    "what_description": "Athenaea velutina is a flowering plant species in the family Solanaceae. It is a shrub or small tree, 3-10 meters tall, with a velvety texture due to the presence of trichomes on its leaves and stems. The leaves are alternate, elliptical to ovate, 8-20 cm long, and 2-6 cm wide, with a pointed apex and entire margin. The inflorescence is a cymose cluster of small, tubular flowers, 2-3 cm long, with a white or yellowish corolla and five-lobed calyx. Athenaea velutina is native to the tropical forests of Central and South America.",
