    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Athenaea velutina are antimicrobial, which is attributed to the presence of saponins and volatile oils, allowing it to inhibit the growth of various bacteria and fungi. The antioxidant properties of this plant are due to flavonoids and phenolic compounds, which help neutralize free radicals and protect against oxidative stress. Additionally, the anti-inflammatory properties are a result of the action of saponins and triterpenoids, which reduce inflammation and alleviate pain, exemplified by its analgesic effects, which are also linked to the presence of flavonoids and phenolic compounds. Furthermore, the antifungal properties of Athenaea velutina are attributed to its ability to inhibit the growth of various fungal species, which is a result of the presence of volatile oils and phenolic compounds. These bioactive compounds contribute to the medicinal properties of Athenaea velutina, rendering it a valuable resource for the development of new medicines.",
